{"id":40,"ayahs":[{"number":246,"arabic":"أَلَمْ تَرَ إِلَى ٱلْمَلَإِ مِنۢ بَنِىٓ إِسْرَٰٓءِيلَ مِنۢ بَعْدِ مُوسَىٰٓ إِذْ قَالُوا۟ لِنَبِىٍّۢ لَّهُمُ ٱبْعَثْ لَنَا مَلِكًۭا نُّقَٰتِلْ فِى سَبِيلِ ٱللَّهِ ۖ قَالَ هَلْ عَسَيْتُمْ إِن كُتِبَ عَلَيْكُمُ ٱلْقِتَالُ أَلَّا تُقَٰتِلُوا۟ ۖ قَالُوا۟ وَمَا لَنَآ أَلَّا نُقَٰتِلَ فِى سَبِيلِ ٱللَّهِ وَقَدْ أُخْرِجْنَا مِن دِيَٰرِنَا وَأَبْنَآئِنَا ۖ فَلَمَّا كُتِبَ عَلَيْهِمُ ٱلْقِتَالُ تَوَلَّوْا۟ إِلَّا قَلِيلًۭا مِّنْهُمْ ۗ وَٱللَّهُ عَلِيمٌۢ بِٱلظَّٰلِمِينَ","translation":"Art thou not aware of those elders of the children of Israel, after the time of Moses, how they said unto a prophet of theirs, \"Raise up a king for us, [and] we shall fight in God's cause\"? Said he: \"Would you, perchance, refrain from fighting if fighting is ordained for you?\" They answered: \"And why should we not fight in God's cause when we and our children have been driven from our homelands?\" Yet, when fighting was ordained for them, they did turn back, save for a few of them; but God had full knowledge of the evildoers.","audio":"https://cdn.islamic.network/quran/audio/128/ar.alafasy/253.mp3","surahId":2,"words":[{"id":86806,"position":1,"arabic":"أَلَمْ","translation":"নি কি","audioUrl":"wbw/002_246_001.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":86807,"position":2,"arabic":"تَرَ","translation":"তুমি দেখ","audioUrl":"wbw/002_246_002.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":86808,"position":3,"arabic":"إِلَى","translation":"প্রতি","audioUrl":"wbw/002_246_003.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":86809,"position":4,"arabic":"ٱلْمَلَإِ","translation":"প্রধানদের","audioUrl":"wbw/002_246_004.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":86810,"position":5,"arabic":"مِنۢ","translation":"মধ্য থেকে","audioUrl":"wbw/002_246_005.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":86811,"position":6,"arabic":"بَنِىٓ","translation":"বনী","audioUrl":"wbw/002_246_006.mp3","charTypeName":"word"},{"id":86812,"position":7,"arabic":"إِسْرَٰٓءِيلَ","translation":"ইসরাঈলদের","audioUrl":"wbw/002_246_007.mp3","c